# Clean Code Rules

General:
- Prefer explicit names.
- Avoid large components.
- Avoid duplicated rendering logic.
- Extract repeated UI into reusable components.
- Keep mock data isolated.
- Keep formatting helpers isolated.
- Do not introduce unnecessary state management.
- Use early returns when useful.

Frontend:
- Use existing MUI components.
- Use existing template className/Tailwind style conventions when present.
- Avoid new global CSS unless necessary.
- Use accessible labels and clear copy.
- Keep Spanish user-facing text for this product.

Prediction UI:
- Display confidence clearly.
- Display risk score clearly.
- Display stake as index, not as bankroll percentage.
- Display NO_BET as a valid professional recommendation.
- Do not promise guaranteed results.
